            h2 School
            p Academics and coursework are a large part of the life of an Andover student, comprising both the school day and an average of 4.2 hours outside of the classroom. The average G.P.A. of respondents was 5.18, which is 0.03 points greater than the average G.P.A. from last year’s survey. In addition to coursework, many students also participate in additional extracurricular activities. 64% of respondents reported that they participated in extracurriculars partly to increase their chances of admission to a selective college, and 7% reported participating in extracurriculars solely for this reason. When looking at college admissions, Andover students are nearly split as to whether attending Andover would increase their chances of admission to a selective college, with 50.9% reporting that it would positively impact their chances and 42.3% reporting that it would negatively impact their chances. Finally, 45% of respondents support a change in the current academic schedule. Earlier this week, faculty voted to adopt a new schedule, Model A3, starting the Fall of 2019.
