            h2 Wellness
            p Addressing student wellness has been at the forefront of Andover’s mission to help students stay balanced. On average, Andover students sleep just under 6.7 hours per night. 78.7% of respondents consider themselves generally happy at Andover, while 63.0% of respondents think that Andover students are happy. The largest percentage of students, 38.5%, find their support system in their friends, with support systems including faculty and/or Sykes staff in addition to friends coming in a close second (33.40%). 166 students have been diagnosed with depression and 187 students have been diagnosed with anxiety, either before or after coming to Andover. 
            br
